## Task 2: Signal Invalidation

When `thesis_valid` flips from True → False, call `invalidate_signals()`:

1. Read `data/gate_signals_today.json` (path: `DATA_DIR / "gate_signals_today.json"` — same as `gate_outcome_tracker.py:21`)
2. Each signal record is a dict. Add `"status": "invalidated"`, `"invalidation_reason": reason`, `"invalidated_at": now.isoformat()`
3. Write back
4. Track previous thesis state so you only invalidate ONCE per flip (not every 15 min)

Also add `"status": "active"` to signals when they're first created in `gate_outcome_tracker.py:log_signal()` — currently no status field exists.

